{"title_page": "Starflower (album)", "text_new": "{{multiple issues|\n{{notability|music|date=May 2017}}\n{{more citations needed|date=April 2017}}\n{{one source|date=August 2017}}\n}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Starflower\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Jennifer Paige]]\n| cover      = JenniferPaige-Starflower.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = March 31, 2017\n| recorded   = 2016\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| length     = 42:47\n| label      = Tone Tree Music\n| producer   = Jeremy Bose\n| prev_title = [[Best Kept Secret (Jennifer Paige album)|Best Kept Secret]]\n| prev_year  = 2012\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Jennifer Paige\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[The Devil's in the Details (Jennifer Paige song)|The Devil's in the Details]]\n | single1date = February 17, 2017\n | single2     = Let Me Love You\n | single2date = March 3, 2017\n | single3     = Forget Me Not\n | single3date = March 17, 2017\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Starflower''''' is the fifth studio album by American pop singer [[Jennifer Paige]], released on March 31, 2017. ''Starflower'' was preceded by the release of three singles, \"[[The Devil's in the Details (Jennifer Paige song)|The Devil's in the Details]]\", \"Let Me Love You\", and \"Forget Me Not\".\n\n==Background==\nPaige partnered with producer Jeremy Bose to begin work on her fourth studio album in early 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jenniferpaige.com/about/ |title=About Jennifer |publisher=Jenniferpaige.com |date= |accessdate=December 27, 2018}}</ref> With a [[crowdfunding]] campaign on [[Kickstarter]], Paige raised almost $35,000 from her fans to cover album production costs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1740294689/jennifer-paige-makes-new-album-daydreamer |title=Jennifer Paige Makes NEW ALBUM |publisher=Kickstarter.com |date= |accessdate=December 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Critical reception ==\nStarflower received positive critical reviews from the music press. Billboard's Andrew Unterberger praised the album as \"one of the early year's best pop full-lengths\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7727876/jennifer-paige-forget-me-not-new-single-premiere-interview |title='90s Star Jennifer Paige Asks 'Forget Me Not' With Excellent New Single & Synth-Pop Comeback Album: Exclusive |publisher=billboard.com |date= |accessdate=March 16, 2017}}</ref> Starflower was also named as one of the 50 best albums of 2017 so far from Billboard.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/photos/7817366/best-albums-2017-top-50-so-far |title=The 50 Best Albums of 2017 So Far: Critics' Picks |publisher=billboard.com |date= |accessdate=June 5, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n! Publication\n! data-sort-type=\"number\"| Rank\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| List\n|-Ad\n| ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''\n| align=center| 21\n| 50 Best Albums of 2017 So Far<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/photos/7817366/best-albums-2017-top-50-so-far |title=The 50 Best Albums of 2017 So Far: Critics' Picks |publisher=billboard.com |date= |accessdate=June 5, 2017}}</ref>\n|-Ad\n| ''Pop Magazine''\n| align=center| 43\n| Best Albums of 2017<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pop-mag.com/best-albums-of-2017 |title=Best Albums of 2017 |publisher=pop-mag.com |date= |accessdate=December 27, 2018}}</ref>\n|-Ad\n| ''[[The Yorkshire Times]]''\n| align=center| 17\n| Top 60 Albums Of 2017<ref>{{cite web |url=http://yorkshiretimes.co.uk/article/Top-60-Albums-Of-2017 |title=Top 60 Albums Of 2017 |publisher=yorkshiretimes.co.uk |date= |accessdate=December 22, 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = ''Starflower'' - {{nobold|&nbsp;Standard edition}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/starflower-mw0003015671|title=Starflower:Music|publisher=Allmusic.com|