{"title_page": "Mersin University", "text_new": "{{Infobox university\n|name           = Mersin University \n|native_name    = Mersin \u00dcniversitesi\n|image          = \n|image_size     = 220px\n|motto          = A world university in the light of science and modernity\n|established    = July 3, 1992 \n|type           = [[Public university]]\n|rector         = K. Suha AYDIN, M.D.<ref>Former rectors Vural \u00dclk\u00fc and U\u011fur Oral</ref>{{full citation needed|date=March 2019}}\n|staff          = 866\n|faculty        = 1405\n|students       = 26,644\n|\n|city           = [[Mersin]] \n|country        = [[Turkey]]\n|colors         = Ultramarine & orange\n                  {{Color box|#1563B8}} {{Color box|#F25C12}} \n|website        = [http://www.mersin.edu.tr/ mersin.edu.tr]\n}}\n\n'''Mersin University''' is a public university, built in 1992 in [[Mersin province]], [[Turkey]]. It has about 25,000 students, 1,405 academic staff, and a number of foreign and guest academic staff.\n\nThe university has research and sports facilities, in [[Mersin]] town centre and in other towns.<ref>{{cite web\n|title=  University of Mersin, Mersin, Turkey  \n|publisher=Math-Net (Russia)\n|year=2009\n|url= http://www.mathnet.ru/php/organisation.phtml?option_lang=eng&orgid=2864\n|accessdate=2009-09-06}}</ref>\n\nIn 2005 the Mersin Technology Development Zone (Technoscope) was set up, creating a partnership between the university's research and development departments and industry, with the aim of developing new technologies that could be directly translated into industrial production.<ref>{{cite web\n|title=  Technoscope  \n|publisher=Mersin Technology Development Zone\n|year=2009\n|url= http://www.technoscope.com.tr/eng/docs/Technoscope_Information_Note_Dec'08.pdf\n|accessdate=2009-09-06}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>\n\n== Departments ==\n\n*Faculty of Engineering\n*Faculty of Economics and Managerial Sciences\n*Faculty of Arts and Science\n*Faculty of Fine Arts\n*Faculty of Water Resources\n*Faculty of Pharmacy\n*Faculty of Medicine\n*Faculty of Architecture\n*Faculty of Educational Sciences\n*Faculty of Tarsus Technical Education\n*Faculty of Communication\n\n==Notable alumni==\n*[[Deniz Sa\u011fd\u0131\u00e7]], artist\n*[[El\u00e7in Sangu]], actress\n*[[Dirayet Ta\u015fdemir]], politician\n*[[Nevin Yan\u0131t]], [[Turkish people|Turkish]] female [[sprint (running)|sprinter]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.mersin.edu.tr/ Mersin University website]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20181123155935/http://www.mersinuniversitesi.net/ Website of Mersin University Students]\n\n{{Universities in Turkey}}\n{{Venues of the 2013 Mediterranean Games}}\n{{Mersin Province}}\n\n{{coord|36.7861|N|34.5258|E|source:kolossus-dewiki|display=title}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1992]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Mersin]]\n[[Category:State universities and colleges in Turkey]]\n[[Category:2013 Mediterranean Games venues]]\n[[Category:1992 establishments in Turkey]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox University\n|name           = Mersin University \n|native_name    = Mersin \u00dcniversitesi\n|image          = \n|image_size     = 220px\n|motto          = A world university in the light of science and modernity\n|established    = July 3, 1992 \n|type           = [[Public university]]\n|rector         = K. Suha AYDIN, M.D.<ref> Former rectors Vural \u00dclk\u00fc and U\u011fur Oral</ref>{{full citation needed|date=March 2019}}\n|staff          = 866\n|faculty        = 1405\n|students       = 26,644\n|\n|city           = [[Mersin]] \n|country        = [[Turkey]]\n|colors         = Ultramarine & orange\n                  {{Color box|#1563B8}} {{Color box|#F25C12}} \n|website        = [http://www.mersin.edu.tr/ mersin.edu.tr]\n}}\n\n'''Mersin University''' is a public university, built in 1992 in [[Mersin province]], [[Turkey]]. It has about 25,000 students, 1,405 academic staff, and a number of foreign and guest academic staff.\n\nThe university has research and sports facilities, in [[Mersin]] town centre and in other towns.<ref>{{cite web\n|title=  University of Mersin, Mersin, Turkey  \n|publisher=Math-Net (Russia)\n|year=2009\n|url= http://www.mathnet.ru/php/organisation.phtml?option_lang=eng&orgid=2864\n|accessdate=2009-09-06}}</ref>\n\nIn 2005 the Mersin Technology Development Zone (Technoscope) was set up, creating a partnership between the university's research and development departments and industry, with the aim of developing new technologies that could be directly translated into industrial production.<ref>{{cite web\n|title=  Technoscope  \n|publisher=Mersin Technology Development Zone\n|year=2009\n|url= http://www.technoscope.com.tr/eng/docs/Technoscope_Information_Note_Dec'08.pdf\n|accessdate=2009-09-06}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>\n\n== Departments ==\n\n*Faculty of Engineering\n*Faculty of Economics and Managerial Sciences\n*Faculty of Arts and Science\n*Faculty of Fine Arts\n*Faculty of Water Resources\n*Faculty of Pharmacy\n*Faculty of Medicine\n*Faculty of Architecture\n*Faculty of Educational Sciences\n*Faculty of Tarsus Technical Education\n*Faculty of Communication\n\n==Notable alumni==\n*[[Deniz Sa\u011fd\u0131\u00e7]], artist\n*[[El\u00e7in Sangu]], actress\n*[[Dirayet Ta\u015fdemir]], politician\n*[[Nevin Yan\u0131t]], [[Turkish people|Turkish]] female [[sprint (running)|sprinter]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.mersin.edu.tr/ Mersin University website]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20181123155935/http://www.mersinuniversitesi.net/ Website of Mersin University Students]\n\n{{Universities in Turkey}}\n{{Venues of the 2013 Mediterranean Games}}\n{{Mersin Province}}\n\n{{coord|36.7861|N|34.5258|E|source:kolossus-dewiki|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Educational institutions established i